On the evening of February 12, the official wechat account of the Affiliated Hospital of Jiujiang College announced that a new case of special COVID-19 pneumonia was confirmed at the Affiliated Hospital of Jiujiang College on February 11. The case had no fever symptoms and was highly occult. Three nucleic acid tests were negative before diagnosis, and the fourth nucleic acid test was positive.

The patient, a 36-year-old woman with a history of living in the affected area, was admitted to the hospital on February 5 with a cough and chest tightness. CT revealed pulmonary inflammation and she was admitted to the hospital with a "viral pneumonia" . Three nucleic acid tests were carried out on February 5,7 and 9, and the results were all negative.

According to the national fifth edition of the COVID-19 infection diagnosis and treatment program, if a patient tests negative for nucleic acid twice (one day apart) , the suspected case can be removed, but if the patient has a history of living in an infected area in Wuhan, chest CT images were more consistent with the change of new pneumonia. The respiratory experts in the hospital did not easily lift the quarantine, and initiated an expert group consultation at the hospital level, which was discussed repeatedly with the chief experts of the imaging department, the Department of Critical Care Medicine and the Department of Medical Laboratory, decided to continue to observe the parallel fourth nucleic acid test, February 11, the test results showed positive.

Director Tong Jianlin, head of the Expert Group on diagnosis and treatment of the new coronavirus at Jiujiang College Affiliated Hospital, said that the new coronavirus in the case was highly insidious and even confusing. The patient returned to Jiujiang from the affected area on January 21. After more than 10 days of home isolation, he developed cough and mild chest tightness on February 2. He has not had fever, a suspected case of new coronavirus pneumonia was rapidly diagnosed and treated after admission. After several days of treatment, CT scan showed that the inflammation was obviously absorbed and the symptoms basically disappeared.

According to the above source, Tong Jianlin believes that because of the high support of the epidemiological history and CT imaging results, even if the nucleic acid test is negative for many times, the expert group on diagnosis and treatment of new coronary pneumonia still has not given up easily, a fourth nucleic acid test confirmed the diagnosis, setting more stringent requirements for the diagnosis of COVID-19 pneumonia in the affiliated hospital of Jiujiang University.

Tong also said that the case in Jiujiang is only a case, no need to panic, but must continue to maintain personal protection, the case of new Jiujiang pneumonia screening and diagnosis of the case to provide some experience and reference.
